        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 19 at 12:31PM CDT until March 19 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 1231 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Scottsburg, or
near Macomb, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Bardolph, Walnut Grove, Western Illinois University, Sciota, Macomb
Municipal Airport, Good Hope, Scottsburg, Bushnell, Spring Lake,
Prairie City Airport, Prairie City, McDonough County 4-H Grounds, and
Macomb.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for west central
Illinois.

A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
sturdy building.</instruction>
